Running OSU - Micro Benchmarks on ARCHER2, hotlum and Cirrus
============================================================

How to install:
---------------
Set the following environment variables:
* NJOBS         - how many cores to use with make
* DOWNLOADS_DIR - where to download the tar file
* SRC_DIR       - where to unpack the tar file
* PREFIX        - install directory
* CC            - C++ compiler wrapper
* ftn           - Fortran compiler wrapper
* cc            - C compiler wrapper

Run the script with
> bash omb_install.sh

How to run:
-----------

bash run_osu.sh -m <machine> -i $PREFIX

where <machine> is either archer2, hotlum or cirrus and $PREFIX is the install
directory of the benchmarks set during the installation step.

